WING this ahead of time was useful information- for MY TURN in reading this book -- OTHER READERS REVIEWS HELPED GIVE ME A CONTEXT WITH THIS NOVEL....so that, I was able to avoid pitfalls - and get most value. The way I saw the short chapters were a little like short stories WITH A PURPOSE contributing to the GREATER CONTEXT.,\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e....The author drives home the evilness that slavery is. The fact that in 300 pages, Yaa Gyasi covers 300 years-worth of the damaging effects that the 'institution-of-slavery' had on people through personal family stories.....getting a 'glimpse' at each of them.....\u003cbr /\u003eis a remarkable achievement. \u003cbr /\u003e.....The characters feel very real. If I was told ahead of time that this was a true story about real people... I would have believed it. The author allows us to see all sides of slavery ( none of it is a pretty picture).... but she steps back from judgement and allows us to look at the inner demons -of the self absorbed- greedy - misogynistic African and American man. \u003cbr /\u003eGyasi reminds me a little of another great author - another great storyteller who doesn't take sides on issues - even horrific evil issues - rather stays on purpose with his storytelling: T.C.Boyle. A book which comes to mind is 'Tortilla Curtain'. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI don't mean to sound intellectual about this book because it's not where my heart lives.... I was simply trying to support another reader -in ways other readers have helped me. In a book about slavery through generations a with so much to cover, I feel 'communities' ought to read this book together, and talk about it. \u003cbr /\u003eI WAS EMOTIONALLY touched ....THE STORYTELLING IS VERY MOVING .. \u003cbr /\u003e .....at the same time it's an important book. The history of how groups of slavery migrated from Africa to America is informative-- and fills in holes with our own understandings. This novel is both educational and intimately personal.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eOur hearts get filled ....and our minds are thankful!","rating":5,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/597461?shelf=read"},"taggings":[],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1686519312"},"likeCount":222,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":56,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Work:kca://work/amzn1.gr.work.v1.KeSPB2dgpTTQJmuUWkUowQ":{"id":"kca://work/amzn1.gr.work.v1.KeSPB2dgpTTQJmuUWkUowQ","__typename":"Work","legacyId":47113792,"bestBook":{"__ref":"Book:kca://book/amzn1.gr.book.v1.n3s7nX8n5A9Fbg7ZEXPCiQ"},"details":{"__typename":"WorkDetails","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/work/47113792-homegoing","shelvesUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/work/shelves/47113792-homegoing","publicationTime":1465282800000,"originalTitle":"Homegoing","awardsWon":[{"__typename":"Award","name":"PEN/Hemingway Foundation Award","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/128-pen-hemingway-foundation-award","awardedAt":1483257600000,"category":null,"hasWon":true},{"__typename":"Award","name":"American Book Award","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/227-american-book-award","awardedAt":1483257600000,"category":null,"hasWon":true},{"__typename":"Award","name":"PEN/Robert W. Bingham Prize","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/1680-pen-robert-w-bingham-prize","awardedAt":1483257600000,"category":"Shortlist","hasWon":false},{"__typename":"Award","name":"Audie Award","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/3572-audie-award","awardedAt":1483257600000,"category":"Literary Fiction \u0026 Classics","hasWon":true},{"__typename":"Award","name":"Dayton Literary Peace Prize","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/award/show/5846-dayton-literary-peace-prize","awardedAt":1483257600000,"category":"Fiction","hasWon":false},{"__typename":"Award","name":"Dylan Thomas Prize","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/award/